{
  "text": "As for bounding k, ModFKV can compute the first k singular values to within a cumulative additive error of\u03b5 \u2225A\u2225 F . This follows from Lemma 2 of [CITATION_1] and the Hoffman-Wielandt inequality. Thus, ModFKV could only conceivably take a singular vector v such that \u2225Av \u2225 \u2265 \u03c3 \u2212\u03b5 \u2225A\u2225 F = \u03c3 (1 \u2212\u03b5 \u2225A\u2225 F /\u03c3 ), and analogously for the upper bound. \u25a1 Proof of Proposition 4.6. We follow the proof of Claim 2 of [CITATION_2] . For i j, we have as follows:",
  "citation_candidates": [
